The trio was arrested as part of a joint operation with the JMPD's K9 Unit, Hawks, Bad Boyz Security, SAPS and Tracker. JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Metro Police have arrested three suspects believed to be part of the infamous Rolex gang. The trio was arrested as part of a joint operation with the JMPD's K9 Unit, Hawks, Bad Boyz Security, SAPS and Tracker. They were nabbed in a red VW GTi and maroon Renault Sandero as they followed a potential victim but were intercepted by the team before they could rob them.